dc_description_s: This data layer represents buildings for St. Croix County, Wisconsin at year-end 2017. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, NSt_Croix_Buildings_2017.gdbN. [The shape and orientation of the ground floor of all structures in a local government. This information is typically compiled from orthoimagery or other aerial photography sources. This representation of the building footprints support the local government basemaps. It also serves as a source for public works, public safety, planning and other agencies that are responsible for the active management of site addresses, facilities, and land use information.]
dct_provenance_s: Arthur H. Robinson Map Library - University of Wisconsin
dc_creator_sm: St. Croix County Land Use, Planning and Development
